cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation of brain tumors. The use of CNNs also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of ROI masks to constrain the networks suggests that it could belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the mention of BraTS2017 suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
